    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>*In nomine sancte et individue trinitatis. <persName
                            key="#Emperor/king #Imperial/royal_diploma #Mansi #Petiae #Landed_possessions #Cereals #Legumes"
                            ref="#people/126">Cunradus</persName> divina favente clementia <rs
                            key="#Emperor/king">Romanorum rex</rs> secundus.* Qui ad sortem Marię
                        concedendo contemplativę vitę tranquillitatem eligunt, activo[rum obsequio
                        tanquam] sedula adrninistratione Marthę in temporalibus sustentari et
                        adiuvari debent. Ea propter omnium tam futurorum quam presentium noverit
                        industria, qualiter nos ob regni [nost]ri firmam stabilitatem et anime
                        nostre dilecteque coniugis nostre <persName key="#Queen" ref="#people/3725"
                            >Gerdrudis</persName>
                        <rs key="#Queen">regine</rs> perpetuam salutem <orgName
                            key="#Monasteries #Abbots #Imperial/royal_diploma #Mansi #Petiae #Landed_possessions #Cereals #Legumes"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/2001">beato Benedicto super Padum</orgName> et
                        fratribus in <rs key="#Monasteries">monasterio</rs> eius deo servientibus
                            <rs key="#Mansi">octo mansos</rs> in <geogName key="#Villas #Mansi"
                            ref="#estates/77"><rs key="#Villas">villa</rs> que dicitur <placeName
                                key="#Villas #Mansi" ref="#places/361">Lectus
                            Paludanus</placeName></geogName> sitos una cum <rs
                            key="#Petiae #Landed_possessions #Cereals #Legumes">tribus agris</rs>
                        <geogName
                            key="#Petiae #Landed_possessions #Production_units #Cereals #Legumes"
                            ref="#estates/2003"><rs key="#Production_units">cellulę</rs>
                            <placeName
                                key="#Petiae #Landed_possessions #Production_units #Cereals #Legumes"
                                ref="#places/2414">Gunzagię</placeName></geogName> adiacentibus
                        donavimus et per presentis <rs key="#Imperial/royal_diploma">privilegii</rs>
                        auctoritatem lege in perpetuum valitura eis confirmavimus edicto regali
                        statuentes, ne aliquis successorum nostrorum regum seu imperatorum aut alia
                        quęlibet persona magna sive parva hanc nostram donationem infringat, sed
                        predicti monasterii <rs key="#Abbots">abbas</rs> et fratres ibidem deo
                        servientes omni futuro in posterum tempore prefatos mansos una cum agris
                        libera et quieta possessione optineant. Si quis autem, quod absit, huius
                        nostre donationis statutum infringere temptaverit, <rs key="#Penalty">centum
                            libras auri purissimi</rs> componat, quarum partem dimidiam <rs
                            key="#Camera_regis">camerę nostrę</rs>, reliquam vero prefato monasterio
                        persolvat. Et ut hec verius credantur et omni deinceps tempore inviolata
                        serventur, hanc inde cartam scribi et sigilli nostri inpressione insigniri
                        iussimus nanuque propria corroborantes idoneos <rs key="#Witness"
                            >testes</rs> subter notari fecimus. Quorum nomina hec sunt: <persName
                            key="#Bishops #Witness #Imperial/royal_diploma" ref="#people/3726"
                            >Egilbertus</persName>
                        <placeName key="#Bishops #Prevosts" ref="#places/1927"
                            >Babenbergensis</placeName>
                        <rs key="#Bishops">episcopus</rs>. <persName
                            key="#Abbots #Witness #Imperial/royal_diploma" ref="#people/3727"
                            >Ra[bbot]o</persName> abbas de <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/2465"
                            key="#Abbots"><placeName ref="#places/4176"
                            >Halsbrunnen</placeName></orgName>. <persName
                                key="#Prevosts #Witness #Imperial/royal_diploma"><name ref="Everardus/prepositus Babenbergensis"
                                >Eberhardus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Prevosts">prepositus</rs> Babenbergensis. <rs key="#Marquis/duke"
                            >Marchio</rs>
                        <persName key="#Marquis/duke #Witness #Imperial/royal_diploma" ref="#people/4019"
                            >Gebehardus</persName>. <persName
                                key="#Other_minor_officer #Witness #Imperial/royal_diploma" ref="#people/4020"
                            >Godefridus</persName>
                        <rs key="#Other_minor_officer">castellanus</rs> de <placeName
                            key="#Other_minor_officer" ref="#places/4177">Nurenberc</placeName>.
                        <persName key="#Witness #Imperial/royal_diploma" ref="#people/4021">Walhterus</persName> de
                            <placeName>Lobe[nhusen</placeName>. <persName
                                key="#Witness #Imperial/royal_diploma" ref="#people/4022">Manegoldus</persName> de
                        <placeName ref="#places/4431">We]rda</placeName>. <persName
                                key="#Witness #Imperial/royal_diploma" ref="#people/4023">Godefridus</persName> de
                            <placeName>Luda</placeName>. <persName
                                key="#Witness #Imperial/royal_diploma" ref="#people/4024">Eberhardus</persName> de
                            <placeName>Hohenstein</placeName>. *Signum domini Cunradi Romanorum
                        regis secundi* M. *Ego <persName key="#Chancellor #Imperial/royal_diploma"
                            ref="#people/3711">Arnoldus</persName>
                        <rs key="#Chancellor" ref="#people/525">cancellarius</rs> vice <persName
                            key="#Archbishops #Archchancellor" ref="#people/3728"
                            >Heinrici</persName>
                        <placeName key="#Archbishops #Archchancellor" ref="#places/2968"
                            >Mogontini</placeName>
                        <rs key="#Archbishops">archiepiscopi</rs> et <rs key="#Archchancellor"
                            >archicancella[rii</rs> regogno]vi.* Data undecimo kal. iunii indictione
                        VIIII, anno dominice incarnationis MCXLVI. Regnante Cuonrado Romanorum rege
                        secundo, anno regni eius VIIII, actum Nuorenberch; in Christo feliciter
                        amen. (S). </ab>
                </div>
